Server Side vs Client Side (ServiceNow)
Server Side	Client Side
Executes on the ServiceNow server	Executes in the user’s browser
Processes data and database operations	Controls UI and user interactions
More secure	Faster user response
Requires server communication	Executes immediately on page
Can access database directly	Cannot access database directly
Used for backend logic	Used for frontend behavior
🔹 Server Side
What is Server Side?

Server-side execution happens on the ServiceNow server and is mainly used for processing data, business logic, and database operations.

Examples
Business Rules
Script Includes
Scheduled Jobs
GlideRecord
Flow Actions
Features
Access database records
Execute backend operations
Secure processing
Handles complex logic
Example Use Case

When an Incident is created → Automatically assign a group and update records.

🔹 Client Side
What is Client Side?

Client-side execution happens in the user's browser and is mainly used for UI interaction and form behavior.

Examples
Client Scripts
UI Policies
UI Actions (Client)
Catalog Client Scripts
Features
Immediate response
No page reload required
Dynamic form updates
Better user experience
Example Use Case

When Priority = High → Show additional fields instantly.

